    "rationale": "This reaction shows the decarbonylation of a simple, acyclic aliphatic aldehyde (heptanal) to its corresponding alkane (hexane) using Wilkinson's catalyst. This is a classic textbook example of the Tsuji-Wilkinson decarbonylation, clearly illustrating the conversion of an R-CHO group to an R-H group. The substrate is simple and avoids other functional groups that could cause ambiguity.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The substrate is a simple aliphatic aldehyde, avoiding aromatic rings which are common in many other named reactions. This specific transformation (aldehyde to alkane) is highly characteristic of this reaction, minimizing overlap with general decarboxylation (from carboxylic acids) or deoxygenation (e.g., Wolff-Kishner, Clemmensen) reactions."
